To test the lexical overlap heuristic utilization in Reading Comprehension models, we create a new test set: Analyzing Lexically Similar QA (ALSQA).

In the case of un-answerable questions, annotators were asked to re-write the question without changing its meaning and maintain the unanswerability reason.3 ALSQA contains 365 questions pairs, 190 with an- swer and 174 without answer.

author: kanishka
description:
COMPS is a dataset of minimal pair sentences in English that enables the 
testing knowledge of concepts and their properties in language models (LMs).
Specifically, it tests the ability of LMs to attribute properties to everyday 
concepts, and demonstrate reasoning compatible with property inheritance, where
subordinate concepts inherit the properties of their superordinate (hypernyms).
